<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="430" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1079]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,440,467]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Rostrum shorter than carapace with 10–13 dorsal teeth and 6–11 ventral teeth. Carapace with dorsal carina on posterior half of midline and with strong ventral carina and with lateral ridge extending from orbit to posterior margin. Abdomen with first somite bearing a blunt barb on anterior margin; Third abdominal somite with dorsal tooth with the tip directed upward. Telson with 20 or more dorsolateral spines (modified by Crosnier 1987a).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="430" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1079]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,584,611]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Distribution</emphasis>
: Western Atlantic: 
<collectingCountry box="[564,637,584,611]" name="Brazil" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[564,637,584,611]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Brazil</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">
<collectingRegion box="[655,728,584,611]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Ceará</collectingRegion>
Chain (seamount), 
<collectingRegion box="[966,1222,584,611]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Norte" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Rio Grande do Norte</collectingRegion>
and Fernando de Noronha Archipelago
</emphasis>
). Indo-Pacific Oceans: Madagascar, Philippines, Indonesia (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1170,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="30.[151,250,622,647]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,174,610]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[280,1308,174,610]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 34. Global geographic distribution of Systellaspis curvispina Crosnier, 1987. Black circles = previous records; star = new record." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3239811/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1079]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,499,656,683]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Bathymetric distribution</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[514,643,656,683]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" unit="m" value="320.0" valueMax="500.0" valueMin="140.0">140–500 m</quantity>
(Crosnier 1987), herein this species was found between 
<quantity box="[1288,1431,656,683]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.95" metricValueMax="11.5" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" unit="m" value="795.0" valueMax="1150.0" valueMin="440.0">440–1150 m</quantity>
, thus extending its bathymetric distribution from deep waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="430" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,152,1079]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,729,755]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Remarks:</emphasis>
According to Crosnier (1987a, b), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crosnier" authorityYear="1987" box="[714,861,729,755]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvispina">
<emphasis box="[714,728,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[743,861,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">curvispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Faxon, 1893" authorityName="Faxon" authorityYear="1893" box="[1096,1362,729,755]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristata">
<emphasis box="[1096,1110,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1125,1211,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">cristata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Faxon, W." box="[1218,1362,729,755]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" pagination="149 - 220" refId="ref18294" refString="Faxon, W. (1893) Reports on the dredging operations off the west coast of Central America to the Galapagos, to the west coast of Mexico, and in the Gulf of California, in charge of Alexander Agassiz, carried on by the U. S. Fish Commission steamer &quot; Albatross &quot;, during 1891, Lieut. Commander Z. L. Tanner, U. S. N., commanding. VI. Preliminary descriptions of new species of Crustacea. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 24, 149 - 220." type="journal article" year="1893">Faxon, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, being slightly differentiated in (characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faxon" authorityYear="1893" box="[592,707,765,791]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristata">
<emphasis box="[592,707,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">S. cristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parentheses): rostrum with 6–11 ventral teeth (
<emphasis box="[1271,1301,766,791]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">vs.</emphasis>
5–8 ventral teeth); dorsal spine on third somite well developed with the tip directed upward (
<emphasis box="[1044,1075,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">vs.</emphasis>
dorsal spine on third somite well developed with the tip not directed upward). Until the present study, only two species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spence Bate" authorityYear="1888" box="[1143,1274,837,863]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1274,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Systellaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was known in Brazilian waters: 
<taxonomicName authority="(A. Milne-Edwards, 1881)" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1881" baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[348,753,873,899]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[348,450,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">S. debilis</emphasis>
(A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards, A." box="[500,745,873,899]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref19746" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1881) Description de quelques crustaces macroures provenant des grandes profondeurs de la mer des Antilles. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, 11, 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1881">Milne-Edwards, 1881</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Filhol, 1885)" authorityName="Filhol" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Filhol" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[807,1103,872,899]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucida">
<emphasis box="[807,939,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">S. pellucida</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Filhol, H." box="[953,1094,872,899]" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" pagination="1 - 301" refId="ref18768" refString="Filhol, H. (1885) La vie au fond des mers. Les explorations sous-marines et les voyages du Travailleur et du Talisman, 1, 1 - 301." type="journal article" year="1885">Filhol, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, however, these species differ by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crosnier" authorityYear="1987" box="[186,332,909,935]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvispina">
<emphasis box="[186,200,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[214,332,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">curvispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the following way (character of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[726,829,909,935]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[726,740,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[754,829,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[882,1006,909,935]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pelucida">
<emphasis box="[882,1006,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">S. pelucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
respectively in parentheses): carapace with two sharp longitudinal lateral carinae (
<emphasis box="[637,660,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">vs</emphasis>
carinae absent) and rostrum with 10–13 dorsal teeth and 6–11 ventral teeth (
<emphasis box="[222,245,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">vs</emphasis>
15 dorsal and 4–10 ventral teeth; 
<emphasis box="[630,653,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">vs</emphasis>
11 dorsal and 5 ventral teeth). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crosnier" authorityYear="1987" box="[1003,1259,981,1007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellapsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvispina">
<emphasis box="[1003,1259,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Systellapsis curvispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded only from Indo-Pacific Oceans (
<figureCitation box="[625,709,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="30.[151,250,622,647]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,174,610]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[280,1308,174,610]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 34. Global geographic distribution of Systellaspis curvispina Crosnier, 1987. Black circles = previous records; star = new record." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3239811/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
), with few records made by Crosnier (1987a, b) in mesopelagic zones. Thus, this paper comprises the first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crosnier" authorityYear="1987" box="[738,884,1053,1079]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellapsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvispina">
<emphasis box="[738,752,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[766,884,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">curvispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Atlantic Ocean (Brazilian waters).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
